@NODE History "History"

 @{b}History of Vinci@{ub}

  Histories for 1.0 to 1.6 removed to save space.

  Version:

   @{" 2.0 " LINK VERS_20}
   @{" 2.1 " LINK VERS_21}
   @{" 2.2 " LINK VERS_22}
   @{" 2.3 " LINK VERS_23}
   @{" 2.4 " LINK VERS_24}
   @{" 2.5 " LINK VERS_25}
   @{" 2.6 " LINK VERS_26}
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_20 "Version 2.0  :  30.1.1996  :  90956 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - Normal text mode removed.
  - Mouse support. @{fg highlight}Niels van Willigenburg@{fg text}.
  - Optimized scrolling routines a bit.
  - ARexx interface. Portname is 'VINCI'.
  - @{b}Load and store@{ub} feature removed. Pretty useless in my eyes.
  - The port for communication between Vincis renamed from 'VINCI' to
    'VINCI.COM'. So remember to replace all copies you have of Vinci and
    Minci unless you want to experience bad, baaaad things.
  - @{b}Index menu@{ub} added. Shows all the files stored.
  - Now shows the filename in the title bar if there is no information
    bar.
  - KEYFILELOCATION environment variable feature removed. Sorry! Place
    your keyfile in either the path where you start Vinci from or in L:.
  - @{b}Load specified@{ub} renamed to @{b}Load from file base@{ub}.
  - Added @{b}Load as AmigaGuide@{ub} feature. Handy if you f.x. want to examine
    a 'C' source which usually does not comply with the width of your
    screen.
  - Added @{b}Load as text@{ub}. Now you can read AmigaGuide files as if were they
    plain text files.
  - Renamed @{b}Quit after last AG@{ub} to @{b}Auto quit@{ub}.
  - Changed @{b}Asynchronous AG handling@{ub} to @{b}View mode@{ub}.
  - Preferences windows do not fallback to Topaz 8 if they can not fit on
    the screen anymore. Instead they try to open a new screen that fits
    their window.
  - @{b}About@{ub} now changes the public screen name if Vinci is on a public
    screen.
  - @{b}Info@{ub}, @{b}Jump to line@{ub}, @{b}Edit ASCII@{ub} and @{b}Edit hex@{ub} features now
    also available to unregistered users. Am I nice or what?
  - @{b}Quote@{ub} feature removed. Pretty useless and actually waste of good
    bytes.
  - Pressing escape will move the window to the back if on a public
    screen.
  - When a match is found after a search it will be placed in the middle
    of the screen instead of in the top. @{fg highlight}Klaus Jensen@{fg text}.
  - Added shortcuts to @{b}Load as AmigaGuide@{ub} and @{b}Load as text@{ub}.
  - Changed in shortcuts @{b}Load specified@{ub} to @{b}Load from file base@{ub}.
    Shortcut key for @{b}Load from path base@{ub} changed to 'P'.
  - Numerous changes to Decrunch preferences. Mostly visual.
  - Added @{b}Auto create@{ub} and @{b}Quiet@{ub} to @{"Decrunch preferences" LINK MI_Decrunching}.
  - Added @{b}Load@{ub} and @{b}Save as@{ub} features to @{b}Preferences menu@{ub}.
    @{fg highlight}Jimmie Bagge@{fg text}.
  - Added shortcut to @{b}Hide@{ub}.
  - Changed the way you scroll in listviews. Refer to @{"Usage" LINK Usage} for detailed
    description. @{fg highlight}Alex Holst@{fg text}.
  - Hundreds of minor but still very important optimizations to keep the
    size down.
  - You may now put the scroller in the left side or completely hide it.
  - Now Vinci will not refresh the text when searching. This means that
    earlier highlighted matches still visible will not be cleared. It also
    means that the annoying flash when showing the search is gone.
  - Added shortcut to @{b}Clear@{ub}.
  - Archive list windows are now also sizable.
  - Every second time you press the popkey Vinci will show the screen from
    which it was opened. Refer to @{"Miscellaneous preferences" LINK MI_Miscellaneous} for detailed
    description. @{fg highlight}Klaus Jensen@{fg text}.
  - Added @{b}Clear and return@{ub} feature. @{fg highlight}Klaus Jensen@{fg text}.
  - Renamed @{b}Special menu@{ub} to @{b}Miscellaneous@{ub} menu.
  - Added @{b}Reload@{ub} feature. @{fg highlight}Klaus Jensen@{fg text}.

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - If a crunched file was decrunched Vinci would wrongly store the
    crunched size.
  - Used the same keyboard shortcut for @{b}Sort@{ub} and @{b}Save@{ub} in the bases.
  - If you pressed return in the string gadget in e.g. file base Vinci
    would update the wrong entry.
  - A couple of bugs regarding scrolling fixed.
  - Used the width of the main window instead of the screen to calculate
    the width of gadgets in base windows. Could lead to a very strange
    GUI.
  - Used the wrong font to write the title in the base windows.
  - Sometimes the popkey would dissappear. @{fg highlight}Alex Holst@{fg text}.
  - Minor bug concerning menu ghosting.
  - Sometimes an AmigaGuide document's window would not open. Hope it is
    fixed now.
  - When using Vinci on/with a screen using 32 or more colors it could
    crash.
  - Minor bug with handling of icons fixed.
  - If Vinci was in "dispatch" mode it would incorrectly dispatch the
    preload entries.
  - Bug in the search routine fixed. Could cause enforcer hits in very
    rare cases.
  - When on a public screen the menus would use the screen font instead of
    the system screen font.
  - Used the wrong font with archive list windows.
  - Forgot to set the busy pointer in the base windows when loading or
    saving entries.
  - Could not load files from a XFH device due to what I believe is a bug
    in XFH. @{fg highlight}Mikkel Kirkgaard Nielsen@{fg text}.
  - Minor problem with the '%s' when selecting editors in preferences.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_21 "Version 2.1  :  4.2.1996  :  90848 bytes"

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - ARexx string bug.
  - Bug in the @{"Flush work path" LINK MI_FlushWorkPath} routine.
  - After loading prefs it would not show the file. @{fg highlight}Jimmie Bagge@{fg text}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_22 "Version 2.2  :  10.2.1996  :  90884 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - Changed the color for search matches from black to white. Makes it
    easier to locate. @{fg highlight}Jimmie Bagge@{fg text}.
  - Instead of using topaz 8 as default font for the screen it now uses
    the system default font.
  - If the search requester is empty it will now copy the last used search
    string. @{fg highlight}Klaus Jensen@{fg text}.

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - ARGH! Will I ever get it right. @{"Flush work path" LINK MI_FlushWorkPath} was broken.
    @{fg highlight}Jimmie Bagge@{fg text}.
  - Used same shortcut for two menuitems.
  - If a display mode was not available Vinci could not open its screen.
    Now it clones the default public screen.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_23 "Version 2.3  :  12.7.1996  :  99816 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - Now supports pipes.
  - Added information windows to the search and formatting functions.
    I therefore got rid of the (in my opinion) annoying flash that occured
    when a search failed.
  - Added History function. Remembers up to the last 999 files loaded.
  - Pressing backspace causes the text to refresh. @{"Keyboard control" LINK Keyboard}
  - Added @{b}Auto close extract window@{ub} feature. @{fg highlight}Jimmie Bagge@{fg text}.
  - Preferences renamed to Settings. More style guide compliant :-)
  - If you have configured Vinci to flush the work path when quitting it
    will now also delete the work directory.
  - The Index menu will disappear if there are no files stored. @{fg highlight}Alex Holst@{fg text}.

  - New support tool: ReFormat.

  - Included Swedish catalog. Translation by Tauno Pinni. More will follow
    when I "soon" get a new E-Mail account. My school is slow on that
    point :-(

  - If you use Executive by Petri Nordlund you will have to exclude Vinci
    from being scheduled because it does not work properly with Executive.
    I do not know why but I will of course try solve this problem.

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - Would crash at startup if a library was missing or there was very
    little memory left. @{fg highlight}Jens Heller S°rensen@{fg text}.
  - The highlighted entry in the archive list window was reset after a
    file was extracted.
  - When checking the length of gadget strings it would sometimes forget
    one or more strings.
  - Removed some enforcer hits that could occur if libraries were missing.
  - If the number of lines exceeded 65535 Vinci would calculate the gadget
    knob position incorrectly when the current line exceeded 65535.
  - If the scroller was positioned in the left side the information gadget
    would be overwritten by the information bar.
  - Minor GUI settings bug.
  - Would crash due to a bewitched algorithm if one of the sizable windows
    were minimized.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_24 "Version 2.4  :  15.9.1996  :  101772 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - Search functions completely rewritten.
  - Uses a Boyer-Moore algorithm for non-wildcard search. Extremely fast!
  - Wildcard search feature added.
  - Search now has a history.

 @{b}Bug fixes@{ub}

  - The @{b}Goto menu@{ub} was broken. @{fg highlight}Ron Coney@{fg text}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_25 "Version 2.5  :  1.4.1997  :  101028 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - Minor tweaks here and there.

 @{b}Notes@{ub}

  - Added new catalogs for Italian, Dutch, Norwegian, Finnish and Swedish.
@ENDNODE

@NODE VERS_26 "Version 2.6  :  4.5.1997  :  101112 bytes"

 @{b}Changes@{ub}

  - Now works with Executive.
@ENDNODE

@NODE ChangeDefaultTool "How to use ChangeDefaultTool"
@{b}
                             ChangeDefaultTool

                   Copyright ę 1995-1996 Martin Wulffeld
                            All Rights Reserved
  _________________________________________________________________________
@{ub}

  1. ChangeDefaultTool

  1.1 - @{" Usage   " LINK CDTUsage}
  1.2 - @{" History " LINK CDTHistory}
@ENDNODE

@NODE CDTUsage "How to use ChangeDefaultTool"

 @{b}Usage@{ub}

  I faced a problem when I had to change from using my old prefered
  textviewer to Vinci. I had literally hundreds of icons which needed
  a new default tool. It would take ages to change them manually so
  instead I wrote a program which I know some of you might find useful.
  It is called @{b}ChangeDefaultTool@{ub} (CDT for short) and is included in
  this distribution.

  You can type 'ChangeDefaultTool ?' to see the command line interface
  of CDT.

  It looks like this:

   F=FILE,A=ALL/S,N=NEWDEFTOOL/K/A,O=OLDDEFTOOL/K,R=REQUESTERS/S


   @{b}FILE@{ub} abbreviation F
   
    The file(s) which icon should have a new icon. Supports pattern
    matching.

   @{b}ALL@{ub} abbreviation A
   
    If specified, subdirectories will be entered too.

   @{b}NEWDEFTOOL@{ub} abbreviation N  (required argument)

    This is the FULL path where the new default tool is. F.x. 'C:Vinci'.
    If there are spaces in the name you will have to put a pair of
    qutation marks around it.

   @{b}OLDDEFTOOL@{ub} abbreviation O

    If you only want certain icons' default tools to be changed you may
    specify default tool names. The various names must be separated by a
    comma.

    F.x. if you specify the following O=C:OldTxtViewer,DH1:GuideReader
    then ONLY the icons with either 'OldTxtViewer' or 'GuideReader' as the
    default tool will be changed.
   
    NOTE: The leading paths 'C:' and 'DH1:' have no effect when comparing
          an icon's default tool with OLDDEFTOOL. Only the executable's
          name is looked at.

   @{b}REQUESTERS@{ub} abbreviation R

    If you specify this option ALL other options have no effect. A file
    requester will appear where you can select the files and drawers you
    wish to change tools for. Then a string requester appears which has
    the same function as the above @{b}OLDDEFTOOL@{ub}. You may enter
    nothing here. The last string requester has the same function as the
    above @{b}NEWDEFTOOL@{ub} except that you do not have to worry about
    spaces in the filename.
   
    Clicking on ChangeDefaultTool's icon will automatically invoke this
    command and you will therefore be prompted with a bunch of requesters.


  Example:
   
   ChangeDefaultTool F=~(#?.info) ALL N=C:Vinci O=SYS:System/AmigaGuide
   
   This will go through all files not having '.info' at the end and enter
   sub directories. When it finds an icon it will check if the default tool
   ends with 'AmigaGuide' and if so change it to 'C:Vinci'.

   In DirectoryOpus you could create a button like this:
   
    ChangeDefaultTool {f} N={RsEnter full filename for new default tool}
    O={RsEnter old default tools (separate by comma)}

    And set @{b}CD source@{ub}, @{b}Do all files@{ub}, @{b}Output window@{ub} and @{b}Rescan source@{ub}.

    Then save configuration and return to the main Opus window. Select some
    files and hit the new button.
@ENDNODE

